          <cite class='member author entry-title unmatched-member'>The Earl of Lindsay</cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I refer the noble Lord to Clause 84 and the definition of "working day". It means:
            <q>every day except&#x2014;
            <ol>
            <li>(a) Saturday and Sunday;</li>
            <li>(b) December 25th and 26th; and</li>
            <li>(c) January 1st and 2nd."</li>
            </ol>
            </q>
            I hope that answers the noble Lord's query.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0564P0-05564'>
        <a name='S5LV0564P0_19950607_GCR_350'>  </a>
